orian" era="ce" normal="1843/1843">1843</unitdate><container id="aspace_baca4a2ab9aff8d9a1517deeb70b9db1" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_f282253a88dabc9d19244cb7409061fe" parent="aspace_baca4a2ab9aff8d9a1517deeb70b9db1" type="folder">17</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_62940ac2599d23a370b4b8062e2b46d4" level="item"><did><unittitle>Tompkins County Election Returns, Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848 . Folder contains returns for various town, county, state, and federal elections held during this period. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>Ithaca Journal</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1836-11-30/1848-11-22" type="inclusive">Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848</unitdate><container id="aspace_6d22004d9b3f3a074633d25122b0193c" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_19cfc3d248811454f738d8add9f2f199" parent="aspace_6d22004d9b3f3a074633d25122b0193c" type="folder">18</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_8a7f96942566fca8837cb11c0479e48f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Articles on slavery, abolition, and colonization, Apr. 5, 1837-Apr. 18, 1838. Folder contains assorted articles on the issues surrounding slavery. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>The Ithaca Journal and Herald</title>.</unittitle><container id="aspace_9e5211224afea5dee59bd8724cc592cd" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_e9519d8c7545f64c12470b14f19fa8a4" parent="aspace_9e5211224afea5dee59bd8724cc592cd" type="folder">19</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_1c38f12fd9778ac3db661a741f138526" level="item"><did><unittitle>Residents of Tompkins County call meeting to discuss fiscal problems they believe caused by politicians in Albany. Article appears in May 7, 1834 <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1834-05-07/1834-05-